The paper deals with the task of generating SQL queries from natural language questions about electronic medical records. This task involves natural language processing, database management, and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and machine learning. The paper also involves database management, which suggests the sub-category cs.DB (Databases). The use of deep learning models for generating SQL queries suggests the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves attention mechanisms and look-up tables, which suggests the sub-category cs.LG (Learning). Finally, the task of information retrieval from natural language questions suggests the sub-category cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
